resources





some resources compiled by other parties. 

a guide
to object technology resources, compiled by taligent corporation. covers
all aspects of object technology.

ibm object technology,
an overview of the products of ibm's object research.

cotar home page,
centre for object technology applications and research (cotar) at the university
of technology, sydney.







papers





these are some papers which you should look at. they represent current
views and research on oo technology, and as such are probably better references
than your texts. 

the end
of objects and the last programmer, by grady booch 

the design
of reusable class libraries, by grady booch 

an
introduction to object technology, a paper on ibm's object research.

the overselling
of object technology, or how to fail on your first object project,
by jan steinman.

north texas society
for object technology links.

the object technology framework,
a ucsf project in oo technology.







texts








wang, paul s. c++ with object-oriented programming. pws
publishing, 1994. the primary required text for the course. naturally,
highly recommended.





eli&euml;ns, anton. principles of object-oriented software
development. addison wesley, 1994. an optional, but highly-recommended
text on ood.







